It would have never occurred to me that:<p><pre><code>   for (i = 0; i <= N; ++i) { ... }
</code></pre>
Has a potential bug in it depending on compiler optimizations (where N=INT_MAX, and the results of ++i may or may not be defined - with the compiler using the &quot;UNDEFINED&quot; behavior to ensure that the above loop runs N+1 times.)
